ld possibly happen in the future has already happened. Investors <em>want <=
/em>to believe; it&#8217;s the company&#8217;s job to make them believe.&nb=
sp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; marg=
in: 0 0 1em 0;">That&#8217;s why I&#8217;ve come to love <strong>narrative =
investing</strong>. Narrative investing <em>isn&#8217;t</em> about finding =
the company with the best story; it takes advantage of the collective <stro=
ng>narrative bias</strong> of the market, the tendency of investors to view=
